HEADWORD: Thorite
<hw>Tho"rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called by
Berzelius from the Scandinavian god <ets>Thor</ets>. See
<er>Thor</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a brown to
black color, or, as in the variety <xex>orangite</xex>, orange-yellow.
It is essentially a silicate of thorium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

